insley-roy@publicisgroupe.com", "title": "Chief Procurement Officer", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "Positive (strategic champion, prior Zycus/PwC deployment, made the sole-source selection, FY26 quick-win urgency)", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-06-24"}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF pain fields / MEDDPICC 2.0 Identify pain", "Next Step 2026-06-01", "AIS_Why field"], "narrative": "The buyer has articulated clear qualitative operational pain but no quantified value case has been captured. The pain is process inefficiency: manual email-based contract validation, no dashboard, and no easy visibility into contract status or next steps (SF pain fields, Next Step 2026-06-04). Florence's mandate is a year-end push to demonstrate procurement impact with a quick-win go-live before end of FY26 (AIS_Why, Next Step 2026-06-01), which implies urgency but not a dollar figure. No contract cycle-time, headcount, or compliance-cost number has been stated. Quantifying this in an ROI workshop with Publicis procurement/finance and anchoring the $250K to a savings and speed number remains the open move."}, "champion": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["OpportunityContactRole Florence Tinsley-Roy (Decision Maker)", "Activity contacts: Emeline Le Foyer", "Next Step 2026-06-29 / 2026-06-12", "Email 2026-07-01 Emeline requesting call"], "narrative": "There are two champions. Florence Tinsley-Roy (CPO, Decision Maker) is the strategic champion: she selected Zycus sole-source, has prior Zycus deployment experience from PwC, and set the quick-win urgency. Emeline Le Foyer (Global IT Procurement Director) is the operational champion who drives the deal daily - 'super pushy', ran 4+ OF1 iterations, handled the BAFO, and pulls Zycus for calls (requested Friday/Monday call, 2026-07-01). What has strengthened since last sweep: the internal blockers cleared (legal resolved, functional doc delivered, Stephen Cook and Paras re-engaged for the 2026-07-06 workshop). What is still missing: Florence's explicit sign-off on the final commercial package and on keeping Merlin as core rather than an option."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Next Step 2026-06-29 (Merlin core vs option)", "AIS_Why (sole-source, PwC blueprint)", "SF competitor fields (none logged)"], "narrative": "There is no external competitor: Publicis selected Zycus sole-source with no RFP, on a partner introduction and Florence's PwC track record. The only competitive pressure is internal. First, status-quo / do-nothing risk, which is low given the stated pain and Florence's year-end quick-win mandate. Second, and more current, internal de-scoping: Emeline is pushing to move Merlin for iContract from core module to an option, a roughly $50K TCV swing (Next Step 2026-06-29), which also erodes the AI differentiation. We win by keeping Merlin core, tying its contract-intelligence and agentic-intake value to the confirmed pain (visibility, process mess) and the quick-win go-live, and getting Florence to bless the scope."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["SF pain field / MEDDPICC 2.0 Identify pain", "Next Step 2026-06-04", "Next Step 2026-06-01"], "narrative": "The confirmed pain is a broken manual contract-management process owned by procurement: 'Actual contractual process is a mess / Email validation / No dashboard / No possibility to know easily what are the next steps' (SF pain field / Next Step 2026-06-04). The remedy scoped is iContract for centralised CLM, iRequest for request/approval automation, and Merlin for contract intelligence and visibility. The pain owner is Florence (CPO) and her procurement team, and her year-end mandate to show impact with a quick win before end of FY26 gives the pain a clock. It is confirmed but qualitative; the financial magnitude has not been quantified."}, "paper_process": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Email 2026-06-29/30 MSA all clauses resolved", 